The Boards of Oya Food Nigeria on Friday announced its decision to take over Black Purist ECO Limited in a deal that will create Nigeria’s strongest food and agribusiness marketing company on a mission to build great consumer packaged food brands that Nigerians will surely love. In a press statement, Oya Food Nigeria and Black Purist ECO Ltd will operate under the new Oya Food Nigeria brand from June 1, 2022. In February, Oya Food Nigeria had agreed to buy mid-tier communications company Black Purist ECO LTD with cash and shares. And, on the other hand, Black Purist ECO shareholders approved the takeover on Tuesday. -Advertisement- “Following receipt of our board approval, the merger between Black Purist ECO Ltd and Oya Food Nigeria will proceed as planned. “At this stage, we expect to launch the new enlarged Oya Food Nigeria brand on June 1st,” Oya Food management stated. However, Oya Food Nigeria maintained that based on the agreement reached by the boards of the two institutions, Black Purist ECO shareholders will receive a consideration of N3.13 per share. This comprises N1.00 per share in cash and the allotment of two new Oya Food Nigeria ordinary shares for every seven Black Purist ECO ordinary shares held as of the implementation date. Black Purist ECO LTD affirmed that there was a strong alignment of values and an even stronger vision for agricultural sustainable development and food security in Nigeria shared between the two institutions which make for a stronger rationale for the proposed merger.